  <description type="morphology">Herbage glabrous, not resinous. Leaf blades narrowly elliptic-oblong to elliptic-obovate, 20–50 mm, margins entire. Involucres (5.5–)6–9.5 × 5–7.5 mm. Phyllary apices yellowish to greenish yellow, not aristate, sparsely or not at all gland-dotted, without resin pockets. Florets 19–25; corollas 5–6.5 mm. Cypsela ribs slightly surpassing apices, forming hornlike extensions. 2n = 12.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Aug–Oct(–Nov).</description>
  <description type="habitat">Rocky or sandy soils, sometimes in clay, usually saline, desert shrub communities, sometimes with scattered junipers;</description>
